## Backend audit runner (optional credentials)
##
## Run:
##   npm run audit:backend
##
## The script reads Supabase config from:
## - VITE_SUPABASE_URL / VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY (recommended for this repo)
## - or SUPABASE_URL / SUPABASE_ANON_KEY (aliases)
##
## Optional: provide test users to run functional authorization checks.
## Create these users in Supabase Auth, and ensure their `profiles.role` matches:
## - admin: role='admin'
## - manager: role='manager'
## - employee: role='employee'

# AUDIT_ADMIN_EMAIL=admin@example.com
# AUDIT_ADMIN_PASSWORD=change-me

# AUDIT_MANAGER_EMAIL=manager@example.com
# AUDIT_MANAGER_PASSWORD=change-me

# AUDIT_EMPLOYEE_EMAIL=employee@example.com
# AUDIT_EMPLOYEE_PASSWORD=change-me

